By: Al-Ghazâlî
---
Even if the gnostic were cast into the fire, he would not feel it, because of
his absorption, and if the delights of Paradise were spread out before him, he
would not turn towards them, because of the perfection of the grace that is in
him and his perfect attainment, which is above all else that can be attained.
